metadata.name: Qing Dynasty Faceted Vase with Flower Decoration
metadata.description:
I am happy to present a new auction for this Qing dynasty vase, which stands about 17.5 cm high and comes with its provenance markings on the bottom, and a certificate of authenticity. 

It is an object from the seller's family. Her grandfather took possession of the vase when he was a commander in the Koumintang army in Chongqing in the 1940s. He took it with him to Taiwan in 1949 and the vase was inherited by the current seller. 

The piece is a unique Chinese ceramic vase that opens bidding with a reserve price of 38 ETH.

The NFT is awarded to the highest bidder and certifies the holder to arrange pickup or delivery of the physical item, which is located in Hong Kong. 
Please visit this link for information about the piece: 
https://daobaoarthouse.carrd.co/ 

Winner of the auction will contact editorarthouse@proton.me for arrangement of transfer of the object. Please feel free to email for clarifications or investigations into the piece. We are happy to answer any questions.
